{"DIKA":[{"def":"A kind of food, made from the almondlike seeds of the Irvingia Barteri, much used by natives of the west coast of Africa; -- called also dika bread.","pos":""}],"DIKE":[{"def":"A wall-like mass of mineral matter, usually an intrusion of igneous rocks, filling up rents or fissures in the original strata.","pos":""}],"DIKER":[{"def":"One who builds stone walls; usually, one who builds them without lime.","pos":""}]}